bureaucracy /bjʊəˈrɒkrəsɪ/

(bureaucracies) 

1. N-COUNT A bureaucracy is an administrative system operated by a large number of officials. 官僚体制 

例： State bureaucracies can tend to stifle enterprise and initiative. 国家官僚体制会压抑人的进取心和积极性。 

2. N-UNCOUNT Bureaucracy refers to all the rules and procedures followed by government departments and similar organizations, especially when you think that these are complicated and cause long delays. 官僚作风 [表不满] 

例： People usually complain about too much bureaucracy. 人们通常会抱怨过多的官僚作风。

